# The Tab Suspender - Chrome Extension Project Specification

## 1. Extension Overview

### Primary Purpose
The Tab Suspender is a Chrome extension designed to automatically suspend inactive browser tabs to reduce memory consumption, improve system performance, and extend battery life on laptops and mobile devices.

### Target Audience
- **Power users** with 20+ tabs open simultaneously
- **Professionals** working with resource-intensive web applications
- **Students and researchers** managing multiple reference materials
- **Users with limited RAM** (4-8GB systems)
- **Remote workers** requiring optimal browser performance during video calls

### Use Cases
- Automatic memory management during extended browsing sessions
- Performance optimization for resource-constrained devices
- Battery life extension on mobile devices
- Workflow optimization for tab-heavy users
- System stability improvement during multitasking

### Value Proposition
- **Memory Savings**: Reduce browser memory usage by 60-80%
- **Performance Boost**: Faster tab switching and reduced system lag
- **Battery Extension**: Increase laptop battery life by 15-25%
- **Productivity**: Maintain workflow without manual tab management
- **Customization**: Flexible rules to match individual browsing patterns

## 2. Core Features (Must-Have)

### Automatic Tab Suspension
- **Inactivity Timer**: Suspend tabs after 30 minutes of inactivity (default)
- **Smart Detection**: Exclude tabs with active audio, video, or form inputs
- **Background Processing**: Monitor tab activity without performance impact
- **Visual Indicators**: Clear suspended tab identification with custom favicon

### Manual Controls
- **One-Click Suspension**: Right-click context menu option
- **Bulk Operations**: Suspend all tabs except active/pinned
- **Instant Restoration**: Click suspended tab to restore immediately
- **Keyboard Shortcuts**: Configurable hotkeys for power users

### Whitelist Management
- **Domain-Based Protection**: Never suspend specific websites
- **URL Pattern Matching**: Support wildcards and regex patterns
- **Temporary Exemptions**: Session-based whitelist entries
- **Import/Export**: Share whitelist configurations

### Memory Statistics
- **Real-Time Monitoring**: Current memory usage display
- **Savings Calculator**: Show memory recovered through suspension
- **Historical Data**: Track performance improvements over time
- **Visual Dashboard**: Graphical representation of memory usage

